text.__SUMMARY__: Cyperus alopecuroides is a sedge of the family Cyperaceae that is native to Australia.The perennial and rhizomatous sedge typically grows to a height of 1 to 1.5 metres (3.3 to 4.9 ft). The plant blooms between May and July producing yellow-brown flowers.In Western Australia it is found around lakes and swamps in the eastern Kimberley region.
